ğŸ”¹ What is MetaMask?
MetaMask is a cryptocurrency wallet and gateway to blockchain applications (like Ethereum and DApps).
It allows users to send, receive, and store Ether (ETH) and other ERC-20 tokens.


ğŸ”¹ Security Features
Password protection
Private key and seed phrase backup
Integration with hardware wallets (Ledger, Trezor)
Open-source, trusted by Ethereum users globally.


| No. | Question                                                      | Answer                                                                                      |
| --- | ------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1   | What is MetaMask?                                             | A browser-based Ethereum wallet used for managing, sending, and receiving Ether and tokens. |
| 2   | Why do we use MetaMask in blockchain projects?                | To interact with smart contracts and decentralized apps (DApps) on Ethereum blockchain.     |
| 3   | What is a wallet address?                                     | A unique public identifier (like an account number) used to receive or send crypto.         |
| 4   | What is the recovery phrase (seed phrase)?                    | A 12-word secret phrase used to restore wallet access.                                      |
| 5   | Can you recover your MetaMask wallet without the seed phrase? | No, without it, access is permanently lost.                                                 |
| 6   | What are Gas and Gas Fees?                                    | Gas is the computational cost of transactions; Gas Fee = Gas Used Ã— Gas Price.              |
| 7   | What network does MetaMask connect to by default?             | The Ethereum Mainnet.                                                                       |
| 8   | What are test networks in Ethereum?                           | Networks like Sepolia or Goerli used for testing without real Ether.                        |
| 9   | How do you add Ether to MetaMask on testnet?                  | By using a faucet that provides free test Ether.                                            |
| 10  | What happens if you set very low Gas Price?                   | The transaction will be delayed or may fail.                                                |
| 11  | What are the main components of MetaMask UI?                  | Account name, balance, network selector, and transaction history.                           |
| 12  | What is the difference between a private key and public key?  | Public key = wallet address; Private key = used to sign transactions (keep secret).         |
| 13  | Why is MetaMask considered a non-custodial wallet?            | Because users, not a third party, control their private keys.                               |
| 14  | How can you view Gas details of a transaction?                | Open transaction in MetaMask â†’ Click â€œActivityâ€ â†’ View Gas Fee and Total ETH spent.         |
| 15  | What happens when you send Ether to another address?          | A blockchain transaction occurs, validated by miners/validators, and Ether is transferred.  |



ğŸ§¾ Summary Notes

MetaMask is essential for Ethereum-based experiments.
Every blockchain transaction requires Gas Fee.
You can practice safely using Sepolia Test Network.
Always back up your seed phrase securely.
MetaMask connects directly with Remix IDE for deploying Solidity contracts.


